Create /dev/btrfs-control

The btrfs control device is a character device (major 10, minor 234) used by the
btrfs kernel module for management operations. This command creates it if it is
missing, for example after a minimal system installation or when udev is not
running.

Usage: create-control-device

Options:
  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')
